[normal]David Lawton[bold]: Yes.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Q141 [bold]&#xa0; 
[normal]Mr Binley:[bold] Knowing what you know now, do you not have one scintilla of concern for people who might have invested in this company to their detriment?
[normal]David Lawton[bold]: It is certainly the case—
[normal]Mr Binley:[bold] It is a very simple question
[normal].
[normal] It is either yes or no.
[normal] 
[normal]Chair:[bold] Can you just let him answer?
[normal] 
[normal]David Lawton[bold]: It is certainly the case that it is important investors have confidence in the integrity of the marketplace.
[normal] 
[normal]It is also the case that there is nothing in the FCA regime that ensures that investors never see the value of their investments fall.
[normal] Ultimately, investors have to make—
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Q142 [bold]&#xa0; 
[normal]Mr Binley:[bold] I did not say that.
[normal] 
