[normal]Mr Binley:[bold] One of the stated aims of the FCA is, and I will 
[normal]say
[normal] it again, to protect shareholders from companies that use “corrupt and unethical methods”.
[normal]David Lawton[bold]: There is a distinction between financial crime—we have been talking about some aspects of that—and broader questions about how companies act and behave.
[normal] 
[normal]For example, we are essentially a capital markets regulator in performing this function.
[normal] 
[normal]We are not a broader regulator of companies.
[normal] 
